results.title: UPRN PoC Web Map Greater Manchester v1.1
results.description:
This Web Map contains datasets from multiple data providers, such as Ordnance Survey (OS), United Kingdom Centre for Ecology & Hydrology (UKCEH), Department for Environment, Food & Rural Affairs (DEFRA), Met Office, etc. to provide a proof-of-concept solution for a service that enables streamlined access to government geospatial data through querying on the Unique Property Reference Number (UPRN) level. Users are able to select UPRNs and access the values from the underlying datasets.

The service contains the following data groups:
  • UPRN points
  • Administrative areas
  • Environmental variables from the ClimateJust project
  • Noise pollution data from DEFRA
  • Modelled background pollution data from DEFRA
  • Carbon storage and water supply data from UKCEH
  • Ellenberg Vegetation Indicator data from UKCEH
  • Multiple datasets from Met Office's Air Quality Reanalysis datasets
The above datasets, combined with Ordnance Survey's most up-to-date UPRN register, comprise the basis of an efficient workflow for acquiring localised pollution, vegetation, and administrative information. This, in turn, provides decision makers with enhanced and granular understanding of the connection of different phenomena, resulting in more informed actions on any scale from national to local.
results.snippet: Web Map containing the Proof of Concept Unique Property Reference Number (UPRN) Service for Greater Manchester. It integrates and presents data from several agencies in an easily queriable way, enabling users to access environmental and administrative information on the UPRN level.

results.title: Carbon Storage Web Map (Greater Manchester)
results.description: This data set contains UK-wide maps of ten different among-model ensemble approaches for two services: above ground Carbon stock and water supply. The data for Carbon comes as fourteen TIF maps for above ground carbon storage at a 1-km2 resolution with associated world files: ten approaches, with a double option for two of those, together with maps of variation among models and among ensembles. For water, the data comes as one shapefile with polygons per watershed, each polygon containing these fourteen estimates. For all maps, 600dpi jpg depictions are added to the supporting information. Directory location independent layer files are included to aid scaling and providing the colour palettes. Ensemble output maps were calculated with different approaches following the supporting documentation and associated publication. Uncertainty estimates for these services are included as variation among contributing model outputs and among the employed ensemble approaches. The work was completed under the ‘EnsemblES - Using ensemble techniques to capture the accuracy and sensitivity of ecosystem service models’ project (NE/T00391X/1) funded by the UKRI Landscape Decisions programme. Full details about this dataset can be found at https://doi.org/10.5285/a9ae773d-b742-4d42-ae42-2b594bae5d38
